{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"extension"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Task","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScT"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An asynchronous get-only throwing property wrapper?"}]},{"text":"","level":2,"anchor":"","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Although "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Task"},{"type":"text","text":" qualifies as being a “throwing property wrapper”, and has a lot in common with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Result"},{"type":"text","text":", in particular, it has some key differences to its synchronous cousins."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"First, unlike mutable "},{"code":"Optional","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"s and "},{"code":"Result","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"s, the value of a "},{"code":"Task","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" exclusively makes sense to be "},{"code":"get","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"-only. Although it’s not currently possible in Swift, it might make sense for an asynchronous "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"property"}]},{"type":"text","text":" to be settable—but not the "},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" of a "},{"code":"Task","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Other differences show up when taking mapping methods into account:"}]},{"text":"flatMap \/ map","level":3,"anchor":"flatMap--map","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"With a synchronous wrapper, like ","type":"text"},{"code":"Result","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", mapping can throw a different type of error than the wrapper’s own error type. You can still do that, with ","type":"text"},{"code":"Task","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". But there’s no way to preserve either of the error types, in the resulting ","type":"text"},{"code":"Task","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", in doing so.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Mapping methods have to handle the possibility of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Task"},{"type":"text","text":" failing, or the transformation failing. This requires the transformed "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Task"},{"type":"text","text":"’s error type to be "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"any Error"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"There is an exception:","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the original "},{"code":"Task","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"’s error type is "},{"code":"Never","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", the "},{"code":"Error","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" type of the transformation could, in theory, match the transformed "},{"code":"Task","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"’s."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In practice, this is possible, but only when the transformation also "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"doesn’t","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" throw. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Never"},{"type":"text","text":" can be preserved in the transformed "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Task"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The reason for this is that, unfortunately, while ","type":"text"},{"code":"Task","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"s technically can use any type of error, there is no way to create a ","type":"text"},{"code":"Task","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" whose ","type":"text"},{"code":"Failure","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is anything except ","type":"text"},{"code":"Never","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"any Error","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Hopefully this limitation will be lifted soon.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"flatMapAndMergeError \/ mapAndMergeError","level":3,"anchor":"flatMapAndMergeError--mapAndMergeError","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In theory, these would also be exceptions. An error type should be able to be preserved, if only one is used across the transformation.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"But for now, “merging error” overloads are not be possible.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"mapError","level":3,"anchor":"mapError","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the future, this may be able to provide a true mapping to new ","type":"text"},{"code":"Task","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" type, with a typed ","type":"text"},{"code":"Failure","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". For now, it at least can still transform an error—the result just needs to be erased to ","type":"text"},{"code":"any Error","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"…That is, unless the "},{"code":"Success","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" type is "},{"code":"Void","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and the failure transformation is not throwing. This special case allows for returning a transformed "},{"code":"Task","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" whose "},{"code":"Failure","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"code":"Never","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", instead of "},{"code":"any Error","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". The "},{"code":"Success","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" type"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"There is one special overload of ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMapError","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" which allows for a type transformation ","type":"text"},{"code":"mapError","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" cannot achieve. If the failure transformation is not throwing, you can return a transformed ","type":"text"},{"code":"Task","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" whose ","type":"text"},{"code":"Failure","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"code":"Never","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", instead of ","type":"text"},{"code":"any Error","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"text":"flatMapError","level":3,"anchor":"flatMapError","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"There is one special overload of ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMapError","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" which allows for a type transformation ","type":"text"},{"code":"mapError","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" cannot achieve. If the failure transformation is not throwing, you can return a transformed ","type":"text"},{"code":"Task","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" whose ","type":"text"},{"code":"Failure","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"code":"Never","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", instead of ","type":"text"},{"code":"any Error","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Extended Structure","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Task","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Task","modules":[{"relatedModules":["_Concurrency"],"name":"HMTask"}],"fragments":[{"text":"extension","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Task","kind":"identifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScT"}],"externalID":"s:e:s:ScT6HMTaskE6reduceyqd__qd___qd__qd___xtYaqd_0_YKXEtYaqd_0_YKs5ErrorRd_0_r0_lF","extendedModule":"_Concurrency","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"extension"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/HMTask\/documentation\/HMTask\/_Concurrency\/Task"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/hmtask\/_concurrency\/task"]}],"hi